comments: LaVine (CHI) moves alongside Lillard (POR) and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
The 24 second shot clock expires while the shot is in the air and the ball does not touch the rim. A shot clock violation is correctly called.
Ball (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Powell's (POR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LaVine (CHI) releases from the contact with Lillard (POR) at the end of his drive.
DeRozan (CHI) and Lillard (POR) mutually engage in marginal hand to hand contact as both players attempt to retrieve the rebound.
McCollum (POR) reaches for the ball on his steal attempt and marginal contact occurs to LaVine's (CHI) body, which does not affect his SQBR on the drive.

Ball (CHI) moves into and makes contact with Lillard's (POR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt. The contact occurs after he gathers the ball against his body and a shooting foul is correctly called.
After the pick, Powell (POR) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
McCollum (POR) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
No player touches the ball after LaVine's (CHI) shot hits the rim and rolls out of bounds. The ball is correctly awarded to the Trail Blazers.
Powell (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Ball's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Little (POR) firms up in a screening position in DeRozan's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jones Jr. (CHI) touched the ball before it hit the backboard on Lillard's (POR) driving shot attempt.
Jones Jr. (CHI) makes contact with the ball during Lillard's (POR) driving shot attempt.
Little's (POR) forearm collapses to his body and he absorbs the contact from DeRozan (CHI) at the end of his drive.
Little (POR) maintains a legal guarding position on DeRozan (CHI) at the end of the drive as DeRozan slips and falls to the ground.
DeRozan (CHI) maintains his dribble as he falls to the floor. He then legally stands up and gathers the ball prior to the release of his jump shot attempt.
Little (POR) makes contact with DeRozan's (CHI) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) commits a take foul on Nance Jr. (POR).
Bradley (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Powell's (POR) path and absorbs the contact.
Bradley (CHI) initially establishes himself in Little's (POR) path and then continues to move into Little, which impedes his ability to get around the screen.
Caruso (CHI) makes clean ball contact to deflect the ball away from McCollum (POR) during the rebound.
Ball (CHI) commits a take foul on Little (POR).
During the inbound, Powell (POR) and DeRozan (CHI) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

McCollum (POR) is connected with LaVine (CHI) and marginal contact occurs when he immediately removes his resting hand from LaVine's (CHI) body at the start of his upward shooting motion during the jump shot attempt.
